Class TagWrapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • TagWrapper

  • public class TagWrapper
extends java.lang.Object
    TagWrapper is an implementation of the Wrapper design pattern. This class adds functionality to the Impinj written Tag class. In particular, TagWrapper adds a TagLocation, and a time seen (in Epoch time) to the tag.
    Since:
    2-3-2015
    Version:
    1
    Author:
    Sean Spurlin

    • Constructor Detail

      • TagWrapper

        public TagWrapper()
        Default constructor for TagWrapper. Creates a TagWrapper with all fields set to null.

      • TagWrapper

        public TagWrapper(com.impinj.octanesdk.Tag tag)
        Constructor which takes the input tag and wraps it up. When it does this, it sets the timestamp of the tag to be the current time in milliseconds from the Epoch, and sets the TagLocation to be in the warehouse.
        Parameters:
        tag - The tag which is to be wrapped up
